# Frontend API Rules

> Frontend only. See also: `core.mdc` · `architecture.mdc`

**Stack:** React Query (TanStack Query) + Axios.

## API Paths and Keys

All request paths and query keys live in `src/shared/model/api.ts` as `API_PATHS` and `API_KEYS`. Hardcoding paths or keys elsewhere is forbidden.

```ts
// src/shared/model/api.ts
export const API_PATHS = {
  TODOS: '/todos',
  TODO_BY_ID: (id: string) => `/todos/${id}`,
} as const;

export const API_KEYS = {
  TODOS: ['todos'],
  TODO: (id: string) => ['todos', id],
} as const;
```

## Request Functions

Pure request functions live in `requests.ts` inside the `api` segment of the corresponding slice.

| Layer        | Location                                 |
| ------------ | ---------------------------------------- |
| **entities** | `src/entities/[entity]/api/requests.ts`  |
| **features** | `src/features/[feature]/api/requests.ts` |

Request functions must be pure — no React hooks, no side effects beyond the HTTP call.

## Client Query Hooks

Client-side React Query hooks live in the `api/client/` segment.

**Naming:** `use-[method]-*-query.ts`

```ts
// src/entities/todo/api/client/use-get-todos-query.ts
export const useGetTodosQuery = () =>
  useQuery({
    queryKey: API_KEYS.TODOS,
    queryFn: getTodos,
    ...GET_TODO_LIST_QUERY_OPTIONS,
  });
```

## Server Fetch Actions

Server-side fetch requests live in the `api/server/` segment.

**Naming:** `[method]-*-action.ts`

Export server actions through `api/server/index.ts`.

## Mutation Hooks

Mutation hooks live in the `api/client/` segment.

**Naming:** `[method]-[entity-name]-mutation.ts`

## React Query Constants

Shared query parameters (`staleTime`, `gcTime`, `retry`, etc.) live in `api/constants.ts` within the slice. Use the same constants for both client hooks and server actions.

## Cache Invalidation and Updates

Cache utilities live in the **entity** layer at `entities/[entity]/lib/cache.ts`.

| Operation  | Action                                                                       |
| ---------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Create** | Invalidate the list cache                                                    |
| **Update** | Invalidate the list cache **and** set the updated entity in the detail cache |
| **Delete** | Invalidate the list cache and remove the detail cache entry                  |

```ts
// src/entities/todo/lib/cache.ts
export const invalidateTodoListCache = () => {
  queryClient.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: API_KEYS.TODOS });
};

export const invalidateTodoByIdCache = (todo: Todo) => {
  queryClient.setQueryData(API_KEYS.TODO(todo.id), todo);
  queryClient.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: API_KEYS.TODO(todo.id) });
};
```

On **update**:

```ts
// src/features/update-todo/api/client/patch-todo-mutation.ts
import {
  invalidateTodoListCache,
  invalidateTodoByIdCache,
} from '@/entities/todo';

export const usePatchTodoMutation = () =>
  useMutation({
    mutationFn: updateTodo,
    onSuccess: (updatedTodo) => {
      invalidateTodoListCache();
      invalidateTodoByIdCache(updatedTodo);
    },
  });
```

Call cache utilities in mutation `onSuccess` handlers — not in components.

## Page States

Pages that depend on `use*Query` hooks must handle **loading** and **error** states.

```tsx
if (isLoading && !data) return <Spinner />;
if (isError) return <Error error={error} />;
return <TodosList todos={data} />;
```

## Mutation Error Handling

Async mutation calls must always be wrapped in `try/catch`. Do not use `console.log()` in `catch` blocks.

## File Structure Summary

```
src/
├── shared/model/api.ts
├── entities/todo/
│   ├── api/
│   │   ├── index.ts
│   │   ├── requests.ts
│   │   ├── constants.ts
│   │   ├── client/
│   │   └── server/
│   └── lib/
│       ├── index.ts
│       └── cache.ts
└── features/create-todo/api/
    ├── index.ts
